external_knowledge:
Top industry refers to the industry with the highest number of job postings in each city; 
Required experience is the number of years of experience required for a job; 
Job posting count is the number of job postings in the top industry for each city.

sql:
SELECT posting_id AS "Job Posting ID"
FROM job_postings
ORDER BY posting_id;

SELECT employer_name, industry
FROM employers
ORDER BY industry ASC;

external_knowledge:
Various industries refer to distinct categories that the employers operate in; 
State refers to the geographical location of the employers and their job postings; 
Average base salary is a measure that represents the mean of all base salaries for job postings in a particular industry within a state; 
At least five job postings implies that only groups with five or more job postings are considered in the calculation.
